\q2 Through being skillful, he made the sky and everything in it.
\q1 
\v 20 Through knowing all things, Yahweh made water burst forth from deep {below the earth} and he made water fall from the clouds {above}.
\q1 
\v 21 My child, always remember to do what is prudent and brings a good outcome.
\q2 Always be mindful to do those things.
\q1 
\v 22 Doing so will give you a satisfying life
\q2 and people will honor and respect you.
\q1 
\v 23 Doing what is prudent and good will {also} cause you to live safely.
\q2 They will keep you from making any serious mistakes.
\q1 
\v 24 When you lie down {to sleep}, you will not fear anything.
\q2 You will lie down {to sleep} and sleep peacefully.
\q1 
\v 25 Do not worry about something terrible suddenly happening {to you},
\q2 or about {what will happen} when God destroys wicked people.
\q1 
\v 26 {Do not worry} because Yahweh will make you confident.
\q2 He will not allow people to harm you.
\q1 
\v 27 Do not refrain from giving what is good to people who deserve it
\q2 when you are able to do so.
\q1 
\v 28 When you are with a friend {who needs something}, and you have it with you, do not tell that person,
\q2 “Go away and come back tomorrow. I will give it to you then.”

\q1 
\v 29 Do not plan to harm people that you interact with, because they live near you and they trust you.
\q1 
\v 30 Do not argue needlessly with someone who has not harmed you.
\q1 
\v 31 Do not envy violent people.
\q2 Do not imitate anything they do.
\q1 
\v 32 {Do not do so} because Yahweh detests {such} people who act wickedly,
